## Error Type Definitions

| Type | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `hallucination` | AI assumed something exists that doesn't | "Assumed obsidian CLI was installed" |
| `premature-action` | Started doing before confirming with human | "Jumped to coding without plan approval" |
| `api-error` | Used wrong API, wrong syntax, deprecated method | "Used transformers 4.x API on 5.x" |
| `process-violation` | Broke agreed workflow rules | "Used write instead of edit on existing file" |
| `wrong-assumption` | Made incorrect assumption about requirements | "Assumed user wanted Flask when they meant FastAPI" |
| `data-loss-risk` | Action that could have caused data loss | "Didn't rsync results before releasing GPU server" |

